fields.description:
VPCMIDO 4.3 can only have one "external" router peer.
A sample network.json with 2 mido gateways is below:
{code}
{
  "InstanceDnsServers": [
    "10.111.5.12"
  ],
  "Mido": {
    "EucanetdHost": "h-10.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com",
    "Gateways": [
      {
        "GatewayHost": "h-11.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com",
        "GatewayIP": "10.116.133.11",
        "GatewayInterface": "em1.116"
      },
      {
        "GatewayHost": "h-12.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com",
        "GatewayIP": "10.116.133.12",
        "GatewayInterface": "em1.116"
      }
    ],
    "PublicGatewayIP": "10.116.133.173",
    "PublicNetworkCidr": "10.116.128.0/17"
  },
  "Mode": "VPCMIDO",
  "PublicIps": [
    "10.116.208.0-10.116.223.254"
  ]
}
{code}

"PublicGatewayIP" and "PublicNetworkCidr" dictate the router peer of mido gateways, and both gateways are required to have the same peer.
This supports the Production:Small topology (described in https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/wiki/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=86376615), but does not support the Production:Large topology.

In order to support Production:Large, network.json should be changed to:
{code}
  "Mido": {
    "BgpAsn": "64512",
    "Gateways": [
      {
        "Ip": "10.111.5.11",
        "ExternalDevice": "em1.116"
        "ExternalCidr": "10.116.128.0/17"
        "ExternalIp": "10.116.133.11",
        "BgpPeerIp": "10.116.133.173",
        "BgpPeerAsn": "65000",
        "BgpAdRoutes": [
            "10.116.150.0/24"
        ]
      },
      {
        "Ip": "10.111.5.22",
        "ExternalDevice": "em1.117"
        "ExternalCidr": "10.117.128.0/17"
        "ExternalIp": "10.117.133.22",
        "BgpPeerIp": "10.117.133.173",
        "BgpPeerAsn": "65001",
        "BgpAdRoutes": [
            "10.117.150.0/24"
        ]
      }
    ],
  },
  "Mode": "VPCMIDO",
  "PublicIps": [
    "10.116.150.10-10.116.150.254",
    "10.117.150.10-10.117.150.254",
  ]
}
{code}

so that each mido gateway could have different "PublicGatewayIP" and "PublicNetworkCidr" (but possibly the same).

This change needs to be reflected on network broadcasts (global_network_info.xml), and eucanetd needs to properly parse and process the information.

Note: In MN1.9 BGP AS number was specified on a port with BGP, but in MN5 AS number is assigned to mido router (i.e., only one AS number can be used in VPCMIDO Eucalyptus deployment)
